IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: OPERATES THRIFT STORES AND PROVIDES MANAGEMENT SERVICES TO TAX EXEMPT ORGANIZATIONS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: OPERATES THRIFT STORES AND PROVIDES MANAGEMENT SERVICES TO TAX EXEMPT ORGANIZATIONS.
IRS990.Desc: PROVIDED PROFESSIONAL SERVICES (MANAGEMENT, ACCOUNTING, HUMAN RESOURCES, INFORMATION SYSTEMS, COMMUNITY RELATIONS) FOR TWO RELATED NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATIONS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: RAISED FUNDS THROUGH THRIFT STORES TO SUPPORT THE OPERATIONS OF COMMUNITY HOSPICE INC., A RELATED NONPROFIT CORPORATION. COMMUNITY HOSPICE, INC. USES THESE FUNDS TO PROVIDE SERVICES AND SUPPORT TO THE TERMINALLY ILL AND THEIR FAMILIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX POSITIONS AND CONCLUDED THAT THE ORGANIZATION HAD TAKEN NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT REQUIRE ADJUSTMENT TO THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THEREFORE, NO PROVISION OR LIABILITY FOR INCOME TAXES HAS BEEN INCLUDED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. THE ORGANIZATION IS NO LONGER SUBJECT TO INCOME TAX EXAMINATIONS BY THE U.S. FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL TAX AUTHORITIES FOR TAX YEARS ENDING SEPTEMBER 30, 2014 AND PRIOR.
ALLOCATION TO COMMUNITY HOSPICE, INC. NOT INCLUDED IN EXPENSES IN THE FS.
THESE ARE GRANTS TO A RELATED ENTITY.

RecipientTable.PurposeOfGrantTxt: TO SUPPORT THE MISSION OF COMMUNITY HOSPICE, INC.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL FUNDS ARE DISTRIBUTED TO COMMUNITY HOSPICE, INC., WHICH IS A RELATED ENTITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 6
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMMUNITY HOSPICE INC. IS THE MEMBER OF COMMUNITY HOSPICE MANAGEMENT AND IS A RELATED ENTITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ONE MEMBER WITH THE POWER TO ELECT OR APPOINT ONE OR MORE MEMBERS OF THE GOVERNING BODY. THE MEMBER IS COMMUNITY HOSPICE INC., A RELATED ENTITY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 7B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNANCE DECISIONS BY THE ORGANIZATION MAY BE SUBJECT TO APPROVAL BY COMMUNITY HOSPICE, INC.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEWS THE FORM 990 AND IS PROVIDED WITH AN OPPORTUNITY TO COMMENT ON THE TAX RETURN PRIOR TO ITS FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ALL EMPLOYEES, VOLUNTEERS, AND MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND ADVISORY COMMITTEES WILL SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST DOCUMENT UPON EMPLOYMENT, APPOINTMENT, OR REAPPOINTMENT AT LEAST ANNUALLY AND MONITORED BY THE CORPORATE COMPLIANCE OFFICER, INDICATING THAT THEY HAVE READ AND UNDERSTOOD THE RELEVANT POLICIES AND THAT THEY WILL OBSERVE THEM.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION IS APPROVED BY THE INDEPENDENT BOARD OF DIRECTORS WHERE THE VOTE OF EACH MEMBER IS COUNTED. COMPENSATION ANALYSIS OF SIMILAR ORGANIZATIONS (TAXABLE AND TAX-EXEMPT) WITH RESPECT TO SIZE AND RESPONSIBILITIES OF EACH POSITION ARE COMPARED ANNUALLY. THE PROCESS IS DOCUMENTED IN THE BOARD MINUTES, PERSONAL ACTION FORMS, AND THE EMPLOYEE'S PERSONNEL FILE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES THESE DOCUMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST IN PUBLIC BINDERS.

MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS FROM COMMUNITY HOSPICE, INC., CHI MANAGEMENT, INC. AND COMMUNITY HOSPICE FOUNDATION MAKE UP THE AUDIT COMMITTEE CHARGED WITH THE RESPONSIBILITY OF OVERSIGHT IN CONNECTION TO THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND SELECTION OF INDEPENDENT AUDITORS.
